sentences.english: Last week, our class want to spring outing.
sentences.chinese: 上周，我们的课堂要春游。

sentences.english: I also take my camera with me when I go traveling or go on spring outings.
sentences.chinese: 当我去旅行或春游的时候我也会带着照相机。

sentences.english: Remember, who agree you this siring outing, hum?
sentences.chinese: 别忘了，是谁要带你们去春游的，嗯？

sentences.english: They are going for a spring outing.
I don't think you can come here before that.
sentences.chinese: 我们去你那里春游踏青好不好？

sentences.english: You whoever wants to go spring outing please sign up your name and pay dues before Friday.
sentences.chinese: 你们谁想参加春游就在星期五之前报名并交费。

sentences.english: We will have a spring outing this Saturday.
sentences.chinese: 我们这个星期六要去春游。

sentences.english: Take a spring walk with your child with a goal of spotting signs of spring.
sentences.chinese: 和你的小孩去春游，找春天去。

sentences.english: Oh , spring outing day at last! It's going to be wonderful.
sentences.chinese: 啊，春游日终于到了，一定会很棒的。

sentences.english: Tomorrow we're going to have spring outing. We're going to Huli Mountain Fortress to see the king of old cannon.
sentences.chinese: 明天我们要去胡里山炮台春游，一睹古炮大王的尊容。

sentences.english: My classmates and I went spring outing last week.
sentences.chinese: 我和我的同学上周进行了一次春游。

sentences.english: That girl he fell for at that outing is now his fiancée.
sentences.chinese: 他在春游中爱上的那个女孩是他现在的未婚妻。

sentences.english: We went to safari park for spring outing.
sentences.chinese: 这次春游，我们去野生动物园玩。

sentences.english: All the boys in the Spring excursion to Peace Park.
sentences.chinese: 和平公园春游时男生们的合影。

definition: lit. tread the green; go for a walk in the spring (when the grass has turned green)/spring hike season around Qingming festival 清明, 4th-6th April
to go for an outing/to go on an excursion
to go for a hike in spring
outing in the country/to go on a hike/to go courting
to cook a meal over a campfire (usu. for a group of people on an outing)/cookout
to enjoy the flowers on a spring outing (idiom)
to enjoy a beautiful spring walk (idiom)
to go on a tour/to have an outing
Children's Day (June 1st), PRC national holiday for children under 14
see 端午節|端午节[Duan1 wu3 jie2]
to amuse oneself/to have fun/to go sightseeing/to take a stroll
